<GUIClass name="CMUI_StopsListTable" id="a9a100c4-b299-48ea-8374-c46972d5a93c">
    <superclass name="CM_BaseTable"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>cnwrl1 17 December 2009 PAR 21889 - CCMS 1002 = Stops and Italian Customs - T1015 = Expiry Date for Stops Clearance

Custom control which has a column which is a listbox.  A collection
can be attached to the control and it will maintain a list of all the
objects checked (self.allSelectedObjects).

Has got an additional column (over the standard list table)
to allow the entry of the Clearance Expiry Date, if and only if
the stops table Allows Clearance Expiry Date to be entered.
</text>
    <DbClassMap file="_usergui"/>
